            <p>That journey revealed something I didn't expect. The problem wasn't that organizations lacked insight, or even that they struggled to execute. The problem was that strategy itself was the wrong shape. It couldn't be delegated. It couldn't be debugged. It couldn't evolve.</p>
            <p>What strategy is needs to change. That's why I'm writing this.</p>
